Politics.headline: Tarique Rahman Sworn In as Bangladesh Prime Minister After BNP's Landslide 2026 Victory
Politics.detail: Tarique Rahman has been sworn in as the Prime Minister of Bangladesh following the Nationalist Party's landslide victory in the recent general election, marking a significant political shift.

Politics.headline: U.S. and Iran hail progress in nuclear talks after Trump threats
Politics.detail: Envoys from the United States and Iran are reporting progress in nuclear talks, which are focused solely on Iran's nuclear program, despite previous threats made by U.S. President Donald Trump.

Politics.headline: U.S. says it will match alleged low-yield nuclear tests by China
Politics.detail: The United States has announced its intention to match any alleged low-yield nuclear tests conducted by China, highlighting concerns about China's rapidly expanding nuclear arsenal.

Politics.headline: Climate Experts Raise Alarm as Government Plans Ministries Merger
Politics.detail: Climate and environmental experts in New Zealand are expressing serious concerns over the government's decision to merge key ministries responsible for climate change and environmental protection into a single mega-agency.

Politics.headline: Emboldened by Election Victory, LDP Demands Key Diet Posts
Politics.detail: Following a significant victory in the February 8 House of Representatives election, Japan's ruling Liberal Democratic Party is now pushing to regain critical parliamentary positions and expedite the passage of the fiscal 2026 budget.

Finance & Economy.headline: UK unemployment rate hits five-year high of 5.2% as wage growth cools
Finance & Economy.detail: The UK's unemployment rate has reached 5.2%, the highest in five years, accompanied by a cooling in wage growth. These figures suggest a potential interest rate cut by the Bank of England in the spring.

Finance & Economy.headline: Goldman Sachs to drop race, gender and LGBTQ+ criteria from board evaluations
Finance & Economy.detail: Goldman Sachs has announced it will no longer consider race, gender, and LGBTQ+ criteria in its board evaluations. This change impacts how the investment bank assesses diversity within the leadership of companies it advises.

Finance & Economy.headline: Gold Price Outlook: Options Sentiment Extreme as Bears Target 4800
Finance & Economy.detail: The sentiment in gold options markets is currently extreme, with bearish positions targeting the 4800 level. This indicates significant downside expectations among some market participants for gold prices.

Finance & Economy.headline: Capital values outpace rental growth: Report
Finance & Economy.detail: A new report indicates that property capital values are increasing at a faster pace than rental growth across various cities in India. This trend is leading to visible yield compression in the real estate market.

Finance & Economy.headline: EU Faces Pressure to Simplify Financial Rules
Finance & Economy.detail: European ministers are pushing for simpler and better banking regulations to ensure sufficient funds are available for investments in the real economy and the modernization of Europe. The ultimate goal is to facilitate investments and economic growth.

Technology.headline: Nvidia to sell Meta millions of chips in multiyear deal
Technology.detail: Nvidia has announced a multiyear deal to sell millions of AI chips to Meta, intensifying competition in the rapidly growing AI hardware market. This comes as Meta also explores developing its own AI chips and potentially using Google's TPUs.

Technology.headline: VodafoneThree supports AI chatbot regulation under Online Safety Act
Technology.detail: VodafoneThree has welcomed the UK government's decision to bring AI chatbots under the Online Safety Act, citing new research that shows almost a third of children view AI chatbots as friends. This move aims to ensure emerging AI technologies used by young people adhere to stronger safety standards.

Technology.headline: AMD partners with TCS on AI tech
Technology.detail: Advanced Micro Devices (AMD) is partnering with Tata Consultancy Services (TCS) to deploy its latest artificial intelligence (AI) data center technology in India, aiming to establish up to 200 megawatts of AI infrastructure capacity. This collaboration challenges Nvidia in India's expanding AI market.

Technology.headline: Virtusa and Wiley partnership to accelerate Wiley's Technology Transformation
Technology.detail: Virtusa Corporation and Wiley have announced a multi-year managed services partnership where Virtusa will provide infrastructure and application services to support Wiley's strategic technology initiatives. This collaboration aims to accelerate Wiley's technology transformation, driving innovation, productivity, and cost efficiencies.

Technology.headline: India eyeing AI data center investments
Technology.detail: India is hoping to attract up to $200 billion in data center investments over the next few years as it aims to become a global hub for artificial intelligence. This initiative underscores the country's strategy to build a robust AI infrastructure and attract foreign capital.

Science.headline: Beyond 'survival' of the fittest: Evolution works in teams
Science.detail: A review of scientific studies suggests that natural selection operates on multiple levels, challenging the common view that evolution is based solely on individual competition.

Science.headline: Solar eclipse shadow visible in Meteosat imagery over Tropical Cyclone Gezani
Science.detail: Satellite imagery captured the shadow of the February 17, 2026, annular solar eclipse as it swept across the southwestern Indian Ocean, partially dimming Tropical Cyclone Gezani west of Madagascar.

Science.headline: Black hole belches radiation long after eating a star
Science.detail: A supermassive black hole, AT2018hyz, unexpectedly began emitting strong radio waves 2.5 years after ripping apart a star and is now 50 times brighter in radio wavelengths than in 2019, with scientists expecting it to keep getting brighter until 2027.

Science.headline: Earthquake Data Provide Solid Footing for AI Foundation Science Model
Science.detail: Scientists are developing 'SeisModal,' an AI foundation model that uses data from the world's largest repository of earthquake information to explore big questions about science, marking a seismic shift in scientific research.

Science.headline: Discovery Could Unlock New Male Birth Control
Science.detail: A recent discovery could pave the way for a new form of male birth control, offering a significant advancement in reproductive health options.

Health.headline: How federal public health funding cuts could affect Minnesota
Health.detail: The article discusses the potential impact of more federal public health funding cuts on Minnesota, with an MPR News host discussing what these cuts could mean and why a federal judge temporarily blocked them.

Health.headline: Disease outbreaks surge in Sudan's capital as war ruins health system
Health.detail: Epidemics and childhood diseases are rapidly increasing across Sudan's Khartoum state due to nearly three years of conflict devastating the healthcare system, causing severe shortages of medicines and damaged infrastructure.

Health.headline: Air Quality Health Advisory Issued for New York City Metro Region
Health.detail: The New York State Department of Environmental Conservation and Department of Health have issued an Air Quality Health Advisory for fine particulate matter in the NYC Metro region for Wednesday, February 18, 2026, due to light winds and limited atmospheric mixing.
Health.source: New York State Department of Environmental Conservation (DEC)

Health.headline: Government of Canada to announce funding under the Emergency Treatment Fund in Northern Ontario
Health.detail: Terry Sheehan, Member of Parliament for Sault Ste. Marie—Algoma, will make an important announcement on behalf of the Minister of Health regarding funding under the Emergency Treatment Fund in Northern Ontario today.

Health.headline: 14 fresh dengue cases detected overnight
Health.detail: Health officials in Bangladesh today reported 14 new cases of dengue in the past 24 hours, with nine hospitalizations in Barishal division, four in Khulna, and one in Rajshahi.

Sports.headline: Indra braves snowstorm for training run
Sports.detail: Australian Olympic hopeful Indra Brown, celebrating her 16th birthday last month, has completed her first training run on the Olympic Halfpipe at Milano Cortina 2026 despite snowy conditions and freezing temperatures. Brown, ranked number one in the Freeski Park and Pipe World Cup standings, is set to begin her Olympic campaign with qualifiers on February 19.

Sports.headline: USF Primed for Battle with Gonzaga at Chase Center
Sports.detail: The University of San Francisco (USF) men's basketball team is preparing to face No. 11/8 Gonzaga for their final West Coast Conference showdown at Chase Center on Wednesday night. USF enters the game with a 15-13 record, recently snapping a three-game skid with a 92-79 victory over San Diego.

Sports.headline: 'Talk about it all the time': Tigers star's honest admission on dream that could see him switch clubs
Sports.detail: Wests Tigers front-rower Fonua Pole has openly discussed the challenges of his 2025 rugby league season, which was cut short by an MCL injury. He also shared his long-held dream of potentially reuniting with his younger brother at the Melbourne Storm in the future.

Sports.headline: Questions over Auston Matthews' leadership dismissed strongly as Team USA prepares for quarterfinal clash with Sweden
Sports.detail: As Team USA men's hockey prepares for a crucial quarterfinal match against Sweden in the Winter Olympics on February 18, questions regarding captain Auston Matthews' leadership have been firmly dismissed by insiders. This knockout stage game at Milano Santagiulia Ice Hockey Arena is seen as a significant test for both Matthews and the team.

Sports.headline: Jake Armsey's Career-High Five RBI Sparks Offense, Backing Strong Pitching in 17-0 Shutout Victory over Western Carolina
Sports.detail: Jake Armsey delivered a career-high five RBIs, including an RBI single and a three-run homer, to lead USC Upstate to a dominant 17-0 shutout victory over Western Carolina. The Spartans' offense exploded for 13 runs in the second inning, securing their first shutout win since May 2025.
Sports.source: University of South Carolina Upstate Athletics

Entertainment.headline: Oscar-winning actor Robert Duvall dies at 95
Entertainment.detail: Oscar-winning actor Robert Duvall, known for his iconic roles in films like 'The Godfather' and 'Apocalypse Now,' has passed away at the age of 95.

Entertainment.headline: 'Hannah Montana' 20th Anniversary: Miley Cyrus to Return in Disney+ Special
Entertainment.detail: Miley Cyrus is reportedly set to revive her iconic role for a Disney+ special celebrating the 20th anniversary of the popular show 'Hannah Montana'.

Entertainment.headline: Warner Bros. says reopening talks with Paramount on its buyout offer
Entertainment.detail: Warner Bros. is reportedly resuming discussions with Paramount regarding a potential buyout offer for the media company.

Entertainment.headline: Anil Kapoor drops pictures with French President Emmanuel Macron; netizens say, 'Time for CM Shivaji Rao'
Entertainment.detail: Bollywood actor Anil Kapoor shared photos from his interaction with French President Emmanuel Macron and First Lady Brigitte Macron during their diplomatic visit to Mumbai, sparking reactions from netizens.

Entertainment.headline: Mariah Carey has released her 16th studio album, “Here for It All,” marking a new chapter in her career.
Entertainment.detail: Mariah Carey has unveiled her 16th studio album, 'Here for It All,' an 11-track record that signifies a new phase in her career, blending soulful R&B, ballads, and pop.

Crime & Justice.headline: Judge declares mistrial in Prairieland ICE shooting trial over lawyer's 'politically charged' shirt
Crime & Justice.detail: A federal judge declared a mistrial in the case of nine Prairieland ICE detention center shooting defendants on Tuesday due to a defense attorney wearing a shirt with a "politically charged message" during jury selection.

Crime & Justice.headline: SC State shooting suspect charged
Crime & Justice.detail: An 18-year-old man has been charged with murder in a shooting that left two people dead last week at South Carolina State University. The incident stemmed from a drug deal.

Crime & Justice.headline: Passenger struck by bullet in apparent road rage incident in Salisbury
Crime & Justice.detail: A passenger of a motor vehicle was struck by a bullet following an apparent road rage incident on Sunday afternoon in Salisbury. The victim sustained non-life-threatening injuries.

Crime & Justice.headline: Police identify woman found dead in SLO; homicide suspected
Crime & Justice.detail: Police in San Luis Obispo have identified a woman found dead, and homicide is suspected, though the cause of death has not yet been determined due to the body's advanced stage of decomposition.

Crime & Justice.headline: Man killed family, pets as Bibb County deputies arrived for eviction, authorities say
Crime & Justice.detail: A man reportedly killed his family and pets as Bibb County deputies arrived for an eviction. The coroner is working to contact the victims' family members.

Education.headline: ALCDSB Welcomes New Director of Education
Education.detail: The Algonquin and Lakeshore Catholic District School Board announced the appointment of a new Director of Education on February 17, 2026.

Education.headline: ICYMI: Florida Reaches #1 in Workforce Education
Education.detail: Governor Ron DeSantis announced Florida has achieved the top spot in the nation for workforce education, five years ahead of the 2030 goal set in Executive Order 19-31, reflecting over $12 billion in commitment.

Education.headline: Clark State College Integrates AI Platform 'Assist' into Nursing Programs
Education.detail: Clark State College has adopted 'Assist,' an advanced AI platform, into its nursing programs to enhance teaching and learning, focusing on preparing practice-ready nurses.

Education.headline: Why teacher evaluation keeps missing the mark
Education.detail: Jena Draper discusses why current teacher evaluation methods often fail to achieve their intended goals.

Education.headline: No post-secondary school coming to Maple Ridge-Pitt Meadows
Education.detail: The Maple Ridge-Pitt Meadows region will not be getting a new post-secondary institution.

Lifestyle.headline: SAS launches new routes in Asia
Lifestyle.detail: SAS is expanding its intercontinental offering for the winter timetable 2026/27 with three new long-haul routes from Copenhagen to Dubai, Phuket, and Krabi, strengthening its winter portfolio and reinforcing Copenhagen's role as a global hub.

Lifestyle.headline: Italy Travel Chaos: Massive Train and Airport Strikes to Disrupt Thousands this February
Lifestyle.detail: Italy is facing widespread travel disruptions this February 2026 due to coordinated industrial actions across its transport sector, including 24-hour walkouts by rail staff and protests by ground handling staff at major airports.

Lifestyle.headline: Troubled Sheertex owner finds buyer in Quebec-based hosiery firm
Lifestyle.detail: SRTX Inc., the Canadian company behind resilient Sheertex pantyhose, has found a buyer in Quebec-based A.Y.K. International Inc., aiming to preserve the Sheertex brand and its proprietary technologies.

Lifestyle.headline: Art X Fashion
Lifestyle.detail: The Museum at FIT is opening a new exhibition titled 'Art X Fashion' from February 18, 2026, to April 19, 2026, which explores the sustained integration of fashion and art.

Lifestyle.headline: McKenzie Health System Continues “Healthy Living Together” Series with Menopause Education Session
Lifestyle.detail: McKenzie Health System is hosting a 'Menopause Matters: Thriving Through the Change' education session today, February 18, 2026, as part of its 'Healthy Living Together' series, focusing on women's health and wellness during menopause.

Opinion/Editorial.headline: Prabowo's Defining Test In Gaza – OpEd
Opinion/Editorial.detail: This opinion piece discusses the Indonesian government's initiative to send 8,000 military personnel to Gaza under President Prabowo Subianto, framing it as a humanitarian rescue operation that experts consider a dangerous strategic move.

Opinion/Editorial.headline: EDITORIAL: A new monster in the plastic pollution problem
Opinion/Editorial.detail: This editorial highlights the overlooked impact of vehicle tire pollution as a significant contributor to plastic pollution, urging for its inclusion in global plastics treaty negotiations. It suggests that even the shift to electric vehicles may not address, and could even worsen, this specific environmental issue.

Opinion/Editorial.headline: Motivational myths that mislead
Opinion/Editorial.detail: This opinion piece explores the complexities of human behavior and motivation, challenging common leadership misconceptions about what truly engages employees beyond monetary incentives. It argues for understanding and appreciating individuals rather than relying on generic motivational myths.

Opinion/Editorial.headline: EDITORIAL — A rise in too-young mothers
Opinion/Editorial.detail: This editorial discusses the alarming increase in teenage and underage pregnancies across the Philippines, highlighting the societal burdens and the perpetuation of poverty associated with this issue. It underscores the strain on public services and the cyclical nature of early motherhood without adequate support.

Opinion/Editorial.headline: In the Age of AI, Animal Fables and Editorial Cartoons Return
Opinion/Editorial.detail: This piece explores a new publishing project, "Animal Intelligence," which revives animal fables and editorial cartoons as a means for reflection on humanity in the era of artificial intelligence, ecological collapse, and societal anxiety. The project aims to use allegory and satire to engage with complex subjects that language struggles to articulate in a rapidly changing world.

World.headline: Ukraine, US, and Russia Conclude First Day of Trilateral Peace Talks in Geneva
World.detail: A new round of trilateral peace talks involving Ukraine, the United States, and Russia concluded its first day in Geneva on Tuesday, with negotiations set to continue. Discussions focused on practical issues and potential solutions, although Ukraine accused Russia of undermining peace efforts with fresh strikes prior to the talks.

World.headline: US and Iran Conclude 'Good Progress' in Second Round of Nuclear Talks in Geneva
World.detail: Indirect nuclear talks between Iran and the United States concluded their second round in Geneva on Tuesday with reported 'good progress' towards identifying common goals. However, US Vice President JD Vance stated that Iran had not yet accepted all 'red lines' outlined by President Trump for a diplomatic resolution.

World.headline: U.S. Military Strikes Three Vessels in Eastern Pacific and Caribbean, Killing 11
World.detail: The U.S. Southern Command announced on Tuesday that the U.S. military struck three vessels on Monday in the eastern Pacific and Caribbean, resulting in 11 fatalities. Four people were killed on each of two vessels in the eastern Pacific, and three on a third vessel in the Caribbean.

World.headline: European Lab Tests Confirm Alexei Navalny Poisoned with Rare Toxin
World.detail: Five European countries, including the UK, France, Germany, Sweden, and the Netherlands, have confirmed that European lab tests found the rare toxin epibatidine in Alexei Navalny's body. British Foreign Secretary Yvette Cooper stated that only the Russian government had the means, motive, and opportunity to use such a toxin.

World.headline: Ukraine Recaptures 201 Square Kilometers, Strikes Russian Oil Refineries
World.detail: Ukraine recaptured 201 square kilometers (78 square miles) from Russia between Wednesday and Sunday last week, marking the most significant land gain in a short period since June 2023. Additionally, the commander of Kyiv's drone forces reported that Ukrainian drones have struck nine oil refineries across Russia since the start of 2026.

Zimbabwe.headline: Zimbabwe war veterans challenge Mnangagwa term extension in court
Zimbabwe.detail: Veterans of Zimbabwe's liberation war have mounted a court challenge against proposed constitutional changes that would extend presidential terms from five to seven years, allowing President Emmerson Mnangagwa to stay in office until 2030. They argue that the bill seeks to prolong his incumbency and violates constitutional safeguards.

Zimbabwe.headline: Zimbabwe tames inflation, now the test is keeping it below 10%
Zimbabwe.detail: Zimbabwe's annual inflation rate has fallen below 10% for the first time since 1997, a significant milestone for a nation once synonymous with hyperinflation. The International Monetary Fund appears cautiously optimistic about the stability, expecting inflation to remain in single digits in 2026.

Zimbabwe.headline: Raza hails 'huge achievement' as Zimbabwe reach Super Eight
Zimbabwe.detail: Zimbabwe captain Sikandar Raza has hailed his side's progression to the Super Eight stage of the ICC Men's T20 World Cup 2026 as a landmark moment for the nation, describing the achievement as both humbling and deeply gratifying. Zimbabwe secured their historic first appearance in the Super Eight of a men's T20 World Cup after their rain-affected Group B clash against Ireland was abandoned.

Zimbabwe.headline: Zimbabwe ramps up efforts against water-borne diseases during rainy season
Zimbabwe.detail: The Zimbabwean government is intensifying preparedness for possible outbreaks of water-borne diseases amid the ongoing rains that have caused flooding in some parts of the country. Information, Publicity and Broadcasting Services Minister Zhemu Soda confirmed that while no major outbreaks have been officially declared, risks remain elevated due to current wet conditions.

Zimbabwe.headline: WATCH: Two-year-old 'abducted' at Bulawayo's Meikles Mall
Zimbabwe.detail: A two-year-old child was reportedly abducted at Bulawayo's Meikles Mall in a local incident that has drawn attention. The story was published on February 17, 2026.
